        <h2>Protecting Your Core</h2>

        <p>The simplest way to insulate your vital organs is by getting into a foetal position. Crossing your forearms
          over your chest and bringing your knees up, not only reduces the total surface area of your body that’s
          exposed
          to cold, but also protects your armpits, groin and chest which produce and lose the most heat.</p>

        <p>To enable you to get into the ideal foetal position the jacket has been engineered around two Survival
          Pockets.
          There’s one on either side of your upper chest to slide your hands into. Both pockets fasten magnetically,
          which
          means they’ll only open when you want them to. They’re double-lined for warmth. And they’re also colour coded
          to
          minimise thinking. The white writing on the left forearm lines up with the white bar tab on the right
          pocket.</p>

        <p>Applying heat to your arteries also keeps your core warm. So once you’re in position, Condition Black is
          designed to turn your body into its own heat pack without you doing anything. The jacket is precisely
          constructed to use the warmth of your own body to apply residual heat to your three most important arteries,
          by
          doubling and trebling up materials and body parts at these key points.</p>
      </div>
