          Safire’s response came in a memo to the Chief of Staff just 48 hours before Armstrong touched down. Its title
          read: ‘In Event of Moon Disaster.’</p>

        <p>It proposed that after a Presidential address, NASA should end communication with the men, leaving them to
          either run out of oxygen, or commit suicide, before a clergyman should adopt the same procedure as a burial at
          sea, commending their souls to “the deepest of the deep.”</p>

